p:
We employ the following notation to describe the study design:
– i: one of the 22 strata (municipalities);
– M
i : number of primary sampling units (households) in the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– S
i : number of primary sampling units (households) selected from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– m
i : number of primary sampling units (households) actually enrolled in the study from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– P
i
: number of individuals living within the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22 (census data);
– p
i
: number of individuals actually enrolled in the study from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
